, it has been Gaelicized as <b>Pluincéid</b>."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William Plunket was born about 1335, in Ireland. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs William Plunket."},"et":{"about 1335–":"umbes 1335–Surnud","1337–Female":"1337–Surnud","1355–1390":"1355–1390","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1355":"1355","about 1335":"umbes 1335","about 1355":"umbes 1355","1390":"1390","Ireland":"Iirimaa"},"fi":{"about 1335–":"noin 1335–Kuollut","1337–Female":"1337–Kuollut","1355–1390":"1355–1390","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1355":"1355","about 1335":"noin 1335","about 1355":"noin 1355","1390":"1390","Ireland":"Irlanti"},"fr":{"about 1335–":"environ 1335–Décédé","1337–Female":"1337–Décédée","1355–1390":"1355–1390","1335–Male":"1335–Décédé","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1355":"1355","about 1335":"environ 1335","about 1355":"environ 1355","1390":"1390","Ireland":"Irlande","lifeSummary":"Sir William Plunket est né environ 1335, à Irlande. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs William Plunket."},"de":{"about 1335–":"um 1335–Verstorben","1337–Female":"1337–Verstorben","1355–1390":"1355–1390","1335–Male":"1335–Verstorben","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1355":"1355","about 1335":"um 1